# File: tests/features/267-fix-interact-click-timeout-when-javascript-dialog-opens.feature
#
# Generated from: specs/bug-fix-interact-click-timeout-when-javascript-dialog-opens/requirements.md
# Issue: #267
# Type: Defect regression

@regression
Feature: interact click handles native JavaScript dialog openings
  A click that opens a native JavaScript dialog has succeeded and must not be
  reported as a generic mouse-release protocol timeout.

  @regression
  Scenario: Dialog-opening click does not report generic protocol timeout
    Given a page button synchronously opens a JavaScript alert
    When the user runs "agentchrome interact click" on that button without "--auto-dismiss-dialogs"
    Then AgentChrome does not return a generic "Input.dispatchMouseEvent" timeout
    And the user can proceed to "agentchrome dialog info" and "agentchrome dialog handle"

  @regression
  Scenario: Auto-dismiss path remains successful
    Given the same JavaScript alert button
    When the user runs "agentchrome --auto-dismiss-dialogs interact click" on that button
    Then the command exits 0 with the existing clicked JSON shape
    And no dialog remains open afterward

  @regression
  Scenario: Prompt dialogs are covered
    Given a page button synchronously opens a JavaScript prompt
    When the user clicks it through "agentchrome interact click"
    Then the prompt can still be accepted with "agentchrome dialog handle accept --text <value>"
